%20Working%20On%20Tech%20To%20Prevent%20AI%20Killing%20Machines%20From%20Turning%20Rogue%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon%20is%20working%20to%20address%20vulnerabilities%20in%20its%20AI%20systems%20that%20could%20be%20exploited%20by%20attackers%20using%20visual%20tricks%20or%20manipulated%20signals.%20Their%20research%20programme%2C%20Guaranteeing%20AI%20Robustness%20Against%20Deception%20(GARD)%2C%20has%20been%20investigating%20these%20%26quot%3Badversarial%20attacks%26quot%3B%20since%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20shown%20how%20seemingly%20harmless%20patterns%20can%20fool%20AI%20into%20misidentifying%20objects%2C%20potentially%20leading%20to%20disastrous%20consequences%20on%20the%20battlefield.%20For%20instance%2C%20an%20AI%20could%20mistake%20a%20bus%20with%20passengers%20for%20a%20tank%20if%20it%20were%20tagged%20with%20the%20right%20%26quot%3Bvisual%20noise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20concerns%20come%20amidst%20public%20anxieties%20about%20the%20Pentagon's%20development%20of%20autonomous%20weapons.%20To%20address%20this%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Defence%20recently%20updated%20its%20AI%20development%20rules%2C%20emphasising%20%26quot%3Bresponsible%20behaviour%26quot%3B%20and%20requiring%20approval%20for%20all%20deployed%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20modestly%20funded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gardproject.org%2F%5C%22%3EGARD%20programme%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20made%20progress%20in%20developing%20defences%20against%20such%20attacks.%20They've%20even%20provided%20some%20tools%20to%20the%20newly%20formed%20Defence%20Department's%20Chief%20Digital%20and%20AI%20Office%20(CDAO).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20some%20advocacy%20groups%20remain%20concerned.%20They%20worry%20that%20AI-powered%20weapons%20could%20misinterpret%20situations%20and%20attack%20without%20cause%2C%20even%20without%20someone%20deliberately%20manipulating%20signals.%20They%20argue%20that%20such%20weapons%20could%20lead%20to%20unintended%