n%20the%20relationship%20between%20sociopathy%20and%20anxiety.%20Eventually%2C%20she%20worked%20as%20a%20therapist%2C%20where%20she%20%26quot%3Bearned%20a%20low-key%20reputation%20as%20'the%20sociopath%20therapist%2C'%26quot%3B%20taking%20on%20clients%20with%20sociopathic%20tendencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGagne's%20memoir%20cast%20light%20on%20a%20lot%20of%20misconceptions%20about%20sociopaths%2C%20from%20how%20they%20process%20emotions%20to%20how%20they%20form%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Sociopaths%20do%20feel%20emotions%2C%20just%20not%20%26quot%3Bsocial%26quot%3B%20ones%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESociopaths%20are%20often%20depicted%20in%20media%20as%20devoid%20of%20feelings%20entirely.%20But%20that's%20not%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20feelings%20came%20naturally%20to%20me%2C%20like%20anger%20and%20happiness%2C%26quot%3B%20Gagne%20writes.%20%26quot%3BBut%20other%20emotions%20weren't%20so%20easy.%20Empathy%20and%20guilt%2C%20embarrassment%20and%20jealousy%20were%20like%20a%20language%20I%20couldn't%20speak%20or%20understand.%26quot%3B%20She%20compares%20her%20emotional%20range%20to%20%26quot%3Ba%20cheap%20set%20of%20crayons%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20she%20can%20access%20primary%20colors%20but%20struggles%20with%20%26quot%3Bmore%20nuanced%20hues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20adult%20researching%20sociopathy%20and%20going%20to%20therapy%2C%20she%20learned%20that%20sociopaths%20%E2%80%94%20and%20even%20psychopaths%20%E2%80%94%20can%20feel%20basic%20emotions.%20But%20they%20don't%20experience%20%26quot%3Bsocial%20emotions%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20shame%2C%20remorse%2C%20and%20even%20romantic%20love%2C%20because%20they%20feel%20a%20lack%20of%20attachment%20to%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Anxiety%20drives%20violent%20or%20risky%20urges%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20pop%20culture%2C%20sociopaths%20get%20a%20thrill%20out%20of%20hurting%20and%20manipulating%20others.%20But%20the%20driver%20of%20high-risk%20and%20harmful%20behavior%20is%20more%20complicated%2C%20Gagne%20argues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20describes%20feeling%20a%20%26quot%3Bpressure%26quot%3B%20and%20anxiety%20whenever%20she%20feels%20apathetic.%20%26quot%3BThe%20nothingness%2C%20I'd%20started%20to%20notice%2C%20made%20my%20urge%20to%20do%20bad%20things%20more%20extreme%2C%26quot%3B%20Gagne%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%20book%2C%20she%20tried%20to%20mitigate%20her%20violent%20or%20unlawful%20urges%20by%20committing%20smaller%20risky%20acts%2C%20like%20breaking%20into%20people's%20homes%20or%20temporarily%20stealing%20cars%20from%20drunk%20fraternity%20brothers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20she%20sees%20her%20past%20behavior%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bsubconscious%20drive%20for%20feeling.%26quot%3B%20Doing%20something%20dangerous%20didn't%20actively%20bring%20her%20joy%20as%20much%20as%20relieve%20tension%20and%20stress%20%E2%80%94%20similar%2C%20she%20said%2C%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubtle-signs-you-might-have-ocd-per-psychologist-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOCD%20compulsion%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Unlike%20psychopaths%2C%20they%20can%20shows%20signs%20of%20change%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fsociopath-vs-psychopath%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BSociopath%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bpsychopath%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20often%20used%20interchangeably%2C%20but%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-psychopaths-and-sociopaths-are-different-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20key%20differences%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20make%20matters%20more%20confusing%2C%20they%20both%20fall%20under%20the%20term%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fantisocial-personality-disorder%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eantisocial%20personality%20disorder%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20Gagne%20finds%20unhelpful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20I%20could%20easily%20identify%20with%20most%20of%20the%20traits%20on%20the%20sociopathic%20and%20psychopathic%20checklists%2C%20I%20was%20only%20able%20to%20relate%20to%20about%20half%20of%20the%20antisocial%20ones%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGagne%20was%20diagnosed%20via%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiagnose-whether-youre-a-sociopath-or-a-psychopath-2016-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epsychopath%20checklist%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20scoring%20within%20a%20lower%20range%20indicates%20sociopathy%20more%20than%20psychopathy%20because%20the%20symptoms%20are%20not%20as%20extreme.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20research%20on%20the%20diagnoses%20is%20still%20limited%2C%20Gagne%20says%20experts%20believe%20that%2C%20unlike%20psychopaths%2C%20sociopaths%20can%20feel%20anxiety%20and%20also%20show%20signs%20of%20learning%20right%20from%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20They're%20not%20devoid%20of%20healthy%20interests%20or%20hobbies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESociopaths%20are%20often%20portrayed%20as%20stoic%20loners%20in%20media%2C%20with%20no%20hobbies%20other%20than%20committing%20crimes%20and%20hurting%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20truth%2C%20they%20can%20have%20interests%20and%20hobbies%20just%20like%20anyone%20else.%20In%20the%20book%2C%20Gagne%20describes%20her%20passion%20for%20music%20(particularly%20jazz)%2C%20her%20love%20for%20her%20childhood%20pet%20ferret%2C%20bonding%20with%20the%20kids%20she%20babysits%2C%20and%20becoming%20fascinated%20with%20psychology%20enough%20to%20turn%20it%20into%20a%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20They%20don't%20understand%20why%20some%20things%20are%20%26quot%3Bwrong%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%20book%2C%20Gagne%20explains%20how%20she%20finds%20it%20difficult%20to%20identify%20%26quot%3Bbad%26quot%3B%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20may%20have%20been%20missing%20an%20emotional%20connection%20to%20the%20concepts%20of%20right%20and%20wrong%2C%20but%20I%20knew%20they%20existed%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Because%20she%20can't%20naturally%20feel%20fear%2C%20shame%2C%20guilt%2C%20or%20remorse%2C%20she%20wouldn't%20know%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhen%20she%20was%20doing%20something%20that%20could%20make%20people%20uncomfortable%20or%20scared%2C%20like%20stealing%20or%20stalking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20in%20adulthood%2C%20she%20would%20try%20to%20pay%20people%20back%20when%20she%20felt%20she%20was%20doing%20something%20wrong.%20She'd%20bring%20flowers%20to%20the%20strangers'%20funerals%20she'd%20crash%20and%20fill%20up%20the%20cars%20she%20briefly%20stole%20with%20gas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20time%20someone%20left%20the%20stove%20on%2C%20so%20I%20turned%20it%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20of%20a%20house%20she%20broke%20into.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20my%20way%20of%20trying%20to%20balance%20the%20karma.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20They%20may%20lie%20to%20avoid%20being%20judged%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20common%20assumption%20is%20that%20sociopaths%20always%20lie%20for%20the%20fun%20of%20it%2C%20or%20for%20personal%20gain.%20In%20Gagne's%20case%2C%20she%20says%20she%20often%20lied%20about%20her%20feelings%20just%20to%20fit%20in.%20She%20felt%20claustrophobia%20whenever%20she%20realized%20she%20wasn't%20feeling%20the%20way%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bsupposed%26quot%3B%20to%2C%20she%20says%20in%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20her%20pet%20ferret%20died%2C%20she%20felt%20sadness%20but%20couldn't%20authentically%20sob%20the%20way%20her%20sister%20did.%20Throughout%20her%20childhood%2C%20she%20didn't%20feel%20remorse%20or%20fear%2C%20and%20sharing%20that%20with%20others%20didn't%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20made%20it%20hard%20for%20her%20to%20form%20genuine%20connections%20with%20others%2C%20because%20she%20feels%20