He%20Jiankui%2C%20who%20was%20sentenced%20to%20three%20years%20in%20prison%20after%20revealing%20that%20he%20had%20created%20the%20first%20gene-edited%20children%20says%20he%20has%20returned%20to%20his%20laboratory%20to%20work%20on%20the%20treatment%20of%20Alzheimer's%20and%20other%20genetic%20diseases.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20He%20told%20a%20Japanese%20newspaper%20that%20he%20had%20resumed%20research%20on%20human%20embryo%20genome%20editing%2C%20despite%20the%20controversy%20over%20the%20ethics%20of%20artificially%20rewriting%20genes.%20He%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmainichi.jp%2Fenglish%2Farticles%2F20240329%2Fp2a%2F00m%2F0sc%2F050000c%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMainichi%20Shimbun%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20use%20discarded%20human%20embryos%20and%20comply%20with%20both%20domestic%20and%20international%20rules%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20he%20had%20no%20plans%20to%20produce%20more%20genome-edited%20babies.%20Previously%2C%20he%20had%20used%20a%20tool%20known%20as%20Crispr-Cas9%20to%20rewrite%20DNA%20in%20embryos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20a%20court%20in%20China%20sentenced%20Mr%20He%20to%20a%20three-year%20in%20prison%20for%20breaching%20medical%20regulations.%20This%20followed%20his%20assertion%20in%20the%20preceding%20year%20that%20he%20had%20engineered%20genetically%20modified%20twin%20sisters%2C%20Lulu%20and%20Nana%2C%20before%20their%20birth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20actions%20reverberated%20throughout%20the%20medical%20and%20scientific%20communities%2C%20eliciting%20widespread%20condemnation%20for%20proceeding%20with%20a%20risky%2C%20ethically%20contentious%2C%20and%20medically%20unjustifiable%20procedure%20without%20sufficient%20consent%20from%20the%20involved%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20determined%20that%20Mr%20He%20had%20falsified%20documents%20from%20an%20ethics%20review%20panel%20to%20enlist%20couples%20for%20his%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20He%20allegedly%20utilized%20the%20gene-editing%20technique%20Crispr-Cas9%20to%20alter%20the%20DNA%20in%20the%20embryos%20of%20the%20sisters%2C%20asserting%20that%20these%20modifications%20would%20confer%20immunity%20to%20HIV%20upon%20the%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20He%20continued%20to%20defend%20his%20work%20saying%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bproud%26quot%3B%20of%20having%20created%20Lulu%20and%20Nana%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fscience%2F2024%2Fapr%2F01%2Fcrispr-cas9-he-jiankui-genome-gene-editing-babies-scientist-back-in-lab%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ereported.%20Another%20girl%20was%20born%20through%20the%20same%20experiment%20in%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20the%20newspaper%20that%20he%20hoped%20to%20use%20genome%20editing%20in%20human%20embryos%20to%20develop%20treatments%20for%20rare%20genetic%20diseases%20such%20as%20Duchenne%20muscular%20dystrophy%20and%20familial%20Alzheimer's%20disease%2C%20at%20three%20laboratories%20he%20has%20opened%20since%20his%20release%20from%20jail%20in%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20the%20newspaper%20that%20the%20three%20children%20were%20perfectly%20healthy%20and%20had%20no%20problems%20with%20their%20growth.%20The%20twins%2C%20now%20aged%205%2C%20were%20attending%20kindergarten.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20results%20of%20analysing%20%5Bthe%20children's%5D%20entire%20gene%20sequences%20show%20that%20there%20were%20no%20modifications%20to%20the%20genes%20other%20than%20for%20the%20medical%20objective%2C%20providing%20evidence%20that%20genome%20editing%20was%20safe%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20Mainichi.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20proud%20to%20have%20helped%20families%20who%20wanted%20healthy%20children.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20Mr%20He%20had%20stunned%20the%20world%20by%20claiming%20to%20have%20created%20the%20world's%20first%20genetically-edited%20babies.%20The%20professor%2C%20who%20was%20educated%20at%20Stanford%20in%20the%20US%2C%20said%20the%20DNA%20of%20the%20two%20girls%20named%20Lulu%20and%20Nana%20was%20modified%20using%20CRISPR%2C%20a%20technique%20which%20allows%20scientists%20to%20remove%20and%20replace%20a%20strand%20with%20pinpoint%20precision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Mr%20He's%20actions%20were%20considered%20%26quot%3Bfoolish%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdangerous%26quot%3B%20by%20experts%20and%20a%20Chinese%20court%20found%20him%20guilty%20for%20this%20experiment%2C%20sentencing%20him%20to%20three%20years%20in%20jail%20and%20imposing%20a%20fine%20of%201%20million%20Yuan.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712167560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-01%2F8vmc30t8_china-he-jiankui-reuters_625x300_21_January_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchinese-scientist-who-gene-edited-babies-is-back-in-lab-after-jail-time-5369252%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mr%20He%20has%20resumed%20research%20on%20human%20embryo%20genome%20editing%2C%20despite%20the%20controversy%20over%20the%20ethics%20of%20artificially%20rewriting%20genes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchinese-scientist-who-gene-edited-babies-is-back-in-lab-after-jail-time-5369252%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchinese-scientist-who-gene-edited-babies-is-back-in-lab-after-jail-time-5369252%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchinese-scientist-who-gene-edited-babies-is-back-in-lab-after-jail-time-5369252%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Suspense%20Grows%20Over%20Gandhis'%20Gameplan%20For%20Amethi%2C%20Raebareli%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20announced%20another%20list%20of%20candidates%20this%20evening%20that%20left%20only%20three%20seats%20undecided%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20--%20among%20them%20the%20Gandhi%20stronghold%20Raebareli%2C%20and%20Amethi%2C%20which%20turned%20against%20the%20Congress%2C%20voting%20en%20masse%20for%20BJP's%20Smriti%20Irani%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20filed%20his%20candidature%20from%20Wayanad%20yesterday%2C%20there%20is%20no%20word%20on%20the%20fate%20of%20Amethi%2C%20which%20he%20won%20thrice%20before%20losing%20it%20to%20Smriti%20Irani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaebareli%20had%20its%20sitting%20MP%2C%20Sonia%20Gandhi%2C%20shifting%20to%20parliament's%20Upper%20house%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20desire%C2%A0%20in%20the%20Congress%20that%20Priyanka%20Gandhi%20Vadra%20take%20over%20her%20mother's%20seat%2C%20while%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20make%20another%20effort%20to%20win%20back%20Amethi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20camp%20is%20gleefully%20watching%20the%20situation%2C%20remarking%20that%20Mr%20Gandhi%20is%20not%20too%20keen%20on%20Amethi%20for%20fear%20of%20another%20defeat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gandhis%2C%20they%20also%20point%20out%2C%20are%20not%20frequent%20visitors%20in%20Raebareli%20and%20Amethi.%20Mr%20Gandhi%20passed%20through%20his%20former%20constituency%20during%20his%20recent%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Nyay%20Yatra%2C%20after%20a%20very%20long%20time.%20The%20Gandhis%20do%20not%20even%20have%20a%20house%20in%20the%20constituency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20concern%20that%20in%20case%20the%20Gandhi%20siblings%20decide%20to%20contest%20from%20these%20two%20seats%2C%20their%20long%20absence%20would%20feature%20prominently%20in%20the%20campaign%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20is%20eager%20to%20add%20the%20Gandhi%20bastions%20to%20its%20kitty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%2C%20which%20has%20been%20aiming%20at%20370%20seats%20this%20time%2C%20is%20expecting%20the%20biggest%20chunk%20to%20come%20from%20the%2080-seat%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmriti%20Irani%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20will%20be%20in%20Wayanad%20on%20Thursday%20to%20support%20the%20BJP%20candidate%20--%20the%20party's%20state%20unit%20chief%20K%20Surendran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%