e%20device%20through%20its%20stores%20and%20authorised%20providers.%20Notably%2C%20the%20iPhone%206%20Plus%20came%20out%20in%20September%202014%20along%20with%20the%20iPhone%206%20model.%20It%20features%20a%20bigger%20screen%20than%20its%20predecessor%20and%20also%20supports%20Apple%20Pay.%20More%20importantly%2C%20it%20was%20the%20last%20iPhone%20series%20to%20support%20a%20physical%20headphone%20jack.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20iPhone%206%20is%20still%20available%20in%20many%20countries%20which%20is%20why%20it%20hasn't%20made%20it%20to%20the%20obsolete%20list%20just%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Apple%20has%20added%20the%20iPad%20Mini%204th%20Generation%20to%20its%20%26quot%3Bvintage%26quot%3B%20list%2C%20meaning%20the%20company%20will%20service%20the%20device%20but%20only%20for%20a%20limited%20time%2C%20based%20on%20part%20availability.%20The%20(PRODUCT)%20RED%20iPhone%208%20and%208%20Plus%20colours%20have%20also%20been%20deemed%20%26quot%3Bvintage%26quot%3B%20while%20other%20shades%20remain%20current%20for%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happens%20if%20you%20have%20an%20Apple%20device%20which%20is%20added%20to%20the%20Vintage%20or%20Obsolete%20category%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Apple%2C%20%26quot%3BProducts%20are%20considered%20vintage%20when%20Apple%20stopped%20distributing%20them%20for%20sale%20more%20than%20five%20and%20less%20than%20seven%20years%20ago%26quot%3B.%20This%20simply%20means%20that%20such%20products%20would%20not%20receive%20further%20notifications%2C%20but%20they%20can%20still%20be%20functional%20for%20everyday%20tasks%20like%20browsing%20the%20web%2C%20checking%20emails%2C%20or%20using%20certain%20apps.%20Vintage%20products%20can%20also%20be%20repaired%20by%20Apple%20Stores%20and%20authorised%20service%20providers%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20availability%20of%20parts.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApple%20explains%20about%20obsolete%20products%2C%20%26quot%3BProducts%20are%20consid